      <akn:section eId="sec_1_1162_22">
        <akn:num>1-1162.22</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Additional penalties for public officials.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_1-1162_22_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>In addition to the penalties set forth in § 1-1162.21, the Ethics Board may censure a public official for a violation of the Code of Conduct that the Ethics Board finds to substantially threaten the public trust.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_1-1162_22_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Ethics Board may recommend in such censure that the Council suspend or remove a Councilmember’s committee chairmanship, if any, committee membership, if any, or vote in any committee.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
